    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA257-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi talaimakaṉatu ētañ colli (ET: talaimakaṟku āṟṟiṉatu ētam collit tōḻi) varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante urged for marriage, speaking about HIS reasons.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA257">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            viḷivi laravamoṭu taḷiciṟan turaii</l>
<l>            maḻaiyeḻun tiṟutta naḷirtūṅku cilampiṟ</l>
<l>            kaḻaiyamalpu nīṭiya vāṉuyar neṭuṅkōṭ</l>
<l>            ṭilaṅkuveḷ ḷaruvi viyaṉmalaik kavāa</l>
<l>            ṉarumpuvā yaviḻnta karuṅkāl vēṅkaip </l>
<l>            poṉmaru ṇaṟuvī kaṉmicait tāa</l>
<l>            naṉmalai nāṭa nayantaṉai yaruḷā</l>
<l>            yiyaṅkunar maṭinta vayantikaḻ ciṟuneṟik</l>
<l>            kaṭumā vaḻaṅkuta laṟintu</l>
<l>            naṭunāḷ varuti nōkō yāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from a land of good mountains,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the gold-like fragrant blossoms of the black-trunked Vēṅkai</l>
<l rend="indent2">that had opened [their] bud mouths spread on the stony height,</l>
<l rend="indent">on the wide mountain slope with shining white waterfalls,</l>
<l rend="indent">on the long peaks, sky-high, on which bamboo has grown thick [and] long,</l>
<l rend="indent">on the mountain-side hung with cold, on which clouds rise [and] tarry,</l>
<l rend="indent">sounding splendidly in drops with endless sound,</l>
<l>you have longed [for her].</l>
<l rend="indent4">Have consideration:</l>
<l>you would come at midnight,</l>
<l rend="indent2">knowing that fierce animals roam [there], on the</l>
<l rend="indent">small path glittering with water, where wanderers have become inactive<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">iyaṅkunar maṭinta</term> is slightly cryptic, but presumably it simply refers to the fact that there are no wanderers at night (as also T.V.G. explains it).</note>.</l>
<l rend="indent4">Ah, I ache.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="7b">
    <l>[although] one who longed [for her] you have no consideration:</l>
</lg>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="9b">
    <l>knowing [how your] swift horses proceed<note place="foot">This is rather what one would expect from the formula <term xml:lang="ta">kaṭu mā</term>, but T.V.G. points out that HE usually does not come by the dangerous mountain path at night in a chariot, but that the topos is that of fearful animals roaming there.</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
